416	     * This proves: at the moment the new session is about to be inserted,
417	     * the active count is at most (cap - 1), so the insert brings it to
418	     * exactly cap. The invariant holds within the transaction boundaries,
419	     * not just between them.
420	     *
421	     * NOTE ON TRUE PARALLELISM:
422	     * True parallel DB execution (multiple PHP processes hitting the same
423	     * MySQL instance simultaneously) is not possible in the current PHPUnit
424	     * test environment — PHP is single-threaded and pcntl_fork() is not
425	     * available in all configurations.
426	     *
427	     * Correctness under real concurrency relies on InnoDB locking guarantees:
428	     *   - SELECT ... FOR UPDATE on the user row acquires an exclusive lock
429	     *     held until COMMIT.
430	     *   - A second transaction issuing the same FOR UPDATE on the same row
431	     *     BLOCKS until the first releases its lock.
432	     *   - After unblocking, the second transaction reads committed state
433	     *     (including the first transaction's INSERT).
